<h1>Lists</h1>
<p>
	A list contains a single column of related options (based on the context around it) for the user to choose from.
	Lists can contain text, icons, or both and can expand to multiple lines if needed.
</p>

<section>
	<h2 id="list">List</h2>
	<p>To display a regular list, add <code class="format-code">.wds-list</code> class in your <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> tag.</p>

	{{#component-demo name='list'}}
		{{#wds-list}}
			<li>List element 1</li>
			<li>List element 2</li>
			<li>List element 3</li>
		{{/wds-list}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Parameters</h2>

	<h3>HBS parameters</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>big (boolean)</strong> - Whether or not the list contains big items</li>
		<li><strong>bold (boolean)</strong> - Whether or not list items should be bold</li>
		<li><strong>lines (boolean)</strong> - Whether or not show line separator betweeen items</li>
		<li><strong>linked (boolean)</strong> - Whether or not items are links</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>CSS Classes</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>wds-has-big-items</strong> - Whether or not the list contains big items</li>
		<li><strong>wds-has-bolded-items</strong> - Whether or not list items should be bold</li>
		<li><strong>wds-has-lines-between</strong> - Whether or not show line separator betweeen items</li>
		<li><strong>wds-is-linked</strong> - Whether or not items are links</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="big-list">Big list</h2>
	<p>
		To display list with more space around its elements, add class
		<code class="format-code">.wds-has-big-items</code>.
		This modificator makes padding broader and font size bigger in each element.
	</p>

	{{#component-demo name='list-big'}}
		{{#wds-list big=true}}
			<li>List element 1</li>
			<li>List element 2</li>
			<li>List element 3</li>
		{{/wds-list}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="bolded-list">Bolded list</h2>
	<p>
		To display list with bolded elements, add class
		<code class="format-code">.wds-has-bolded-items</code>.
		This modificator sets <code class="format-code">font-weight</code> to bold.
	</p>

	{{#component-demo name='list-bold'}}
		{{#wds-list bold=true}}
			<li>List element 1</li>
			<li>List element 2</li>
			<li>List element 3</li>
		{{/wds-list}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="list-with-separators">List with line separator</h2>
	<p>
		<code class="format-code">.wds-has-lines-between</code> class
		adds subtle separator between each element of your list.
	</p>

	{{#component-demo name='list-lines'}}
		{{#wds-list lines=true}}
			<li>List element 1</li>
			<li>List element 2</li>
			<li>List element 3</li>
		{{/wds-list}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="list-linked">List with linked items</h2>
	<p>
		For lists with linked elements, like menus, use class
		<code class="format-code">.wds-is-linked</code> â€” it expands <code class="format-code">&lt;a&gt;</code>
		node inside list elements to be fully clickable, without any gaps around.
		It is necessary to remember about adding anchor <code class="format-code">&lt;a&gt;</code>
		wrapping each elements content.
	</p>

	{{#component-demo name='list-linked'}}
		{{#wds-list linked=true}}
			<li><a href="http://wikia.com">Linked element 1</a></li>
			<li><a href="http://wikia.com">Linked element 2</a></li>
			<li><a href="http://wikia.com">Linked element 3</a></li>
		{{/wds-list}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>
